Privacy Policy — Bookmark Chaser
Last updated: 10 July 2026

Bookmark Chaser does not collect, store, transmit, or sell any user data.

What the extension accesses and why
Bookmarks — The extension reads your bookmarks so you can choose which sites to track, and it deletes/recreates a bookmark when a tracked site moves to a new domain. Bookmark data never leaves your browser.
Visited page URLs (tabs permission) — The extension checks the address of pages you visit solely to detect when a tracked site appears on a new domain extension. URLs are not recorded, except that when a tracked site changes domain, the old and new domain names are saved to a local history log you can view and clear at any time.
Local storage — Your tracked-site list and the history log are stored locally on your device using the browser's extension storage. This data is never transmitted anywhere.

What the extension does NOT do
No data is sent to any server. The extension makes no network requests at all.
No analytics, tracking, or advertising of any kind.
No personal information is collected.
No data is shared or sold to third parties.

Data removal
All data is stored locally. Uninstalling the extension permanently deletes everything it stored. You can also clear the history log from the extension popup at any time.
